3300>(1/22/02 1:08:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=81.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://cofk.com/members/kogg.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: public raid</span><hr size=1> I need volunteers for this.  not just talk...<br><br>Even though all officers should be on the look out for good CofK material, An officer dedicated to recruitment is not a bad idea.<br><br>So Who wants to be in charge of recruitment? <br><br>Since we are growing in numbers rather quickly, we need to have some guidelines.<br><br>I suggest:<br><br><br>1.  That we limit any recruitment to characters of level 20 or higher.<br>2.  Recruits be required to visit and read bothe the message board and the web page at cofk.com BEFORE joining.<br><br>These are a couple of ideas that I've heard from the officers and I agree.<br><br>Although, newbies are part of the game.  However many newbies will not fit into the CofK.  <br><br>I think that the most important thing is that new members have a strong knowledge of the game and whether newbie or not...  We all learn the game at our own rate.  Some faster and better than others.  <br><br>I dont want the CofK to be an uber guild.  But, a guild of friends, helpful and supportive when able.<br><br>--- Kogginn --- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/ulananirigger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>lananirigger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#993300>(1/22/02 1:26:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=81.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: public raid</span><hr size=1> a public raid sounds like fun, but remembe